The paper deals with the issue of crosstalk interference in DSL transmission, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the use of linear precoding techniques for crosstalk compensation, which is a topic related to communication systems (cs.COMM) and signal processing (cs.SI). Lastly, the paper provides a design tool for DSL linear crosstalk precoders, which is a topic related to distributed systems (cs.DS).
